## 2️⃣ Main Analysis Results

### Event Popularity and Seasonal Dynamics
- Summer: users mostly attend concerts.  
- Autumn: theater and sports events more popular.  
- Largest seasonal difference in sports events (more viewers in autumn).  

### Device Type and Age Restrictions
- Distribution of orders by device type is stable across seasons.  
- Age restriction distribution is stable, no seasonal skew observed.  

### Average Ticket Price
- Slightly higher in summer than autumn.  
- Biggest increases in summer observed in theater, “Yolki” (New Year shows), and concerts (10–17% higher than autumn).

### User Activity in Autumn
- Daily order counts fluctuate between ~1,000 and 7,000.  
- Active users increased from under 600 in early autumn to 1,300 by late October.  
- Average orders per day: 2–3, with spikes up to 6–7 at the start of the month.  
- Average ticket price stable at 180–200 RUB.  
- By weekday:  
  - Highest order counts: Tuesday and Thursday; lowest: Monday, Saturday, Sunday.  
  - DAU peaks on Thursday, lowest on Sunday (4394–4970 users).  
  - Average orders per user highest on Tuesday (~6.5), lowest on weekends.  
  - Ticket price stable (186–191 RUB), independent of day of the week.

### Regional and Partner Activity
- Top regions by unique events: Kamenevsky, Severoyarskaya, Shirokovskaya, Svetopolyansky.  
- Kamenevsky leads with ~4,000 events (25% of total).  
- Top partners by order volume: “Bilety bez problem”, “Lovi Bilet!”, “Bilety v Ruki”.  
- “Bilety bez problem” accounts for 19% of all orders.

